HEADWORD: Polygalic
<hw>Po*lyg"a*lic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or obtained from, Polygala; specifically,
designating an acrid glucoside (called <xex>polygalic acid</xex>,
<xex>senegin</xex>, etc.), resembling, or possibly identical with,
<xex>saponin</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polygamia</ent>⟦br⟧
